The paper deals with maintaining distances in a graph undergoing edge deletions, which is a problem in data structures (cs.DS) and graph theory (cs.GT). The use of hop sets and bounded-hop SSSP techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to the computational geometry (cs.CG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories. Finally, the mention of approximation algorithms and running time analysis suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the discrete mathematics (cs.DM) sub-category.
